# flow-compose-ts Codebase Context

## Package

- Name: `@execution-flows/flow-compose` (npm)
- Language: TypeScript 5.x; tests with Vitest; build via `tsc` -> `dist/`
- Imports: tests and `flow-function.ts`

## Purpose

This library composes flows from named flow functions. A flow context maps keys to invokers (and optionally `flowArgument` markers). Each invoker receives `runners` and returns a callable runner (`FlowFunction<R>`). Nested composition extends runners via shallow copy so root `flow()` arguments are visible in nested `flowFunction` invokers unless shadowed.

## Source Layout

- `src/flow-compose/types.ts`: Core types including `FlowFunction`, `FlowFunctionInvoker`, `Runners`, `FlowContext`, and marker-driven argument types.
- `src/flow-compose/flow-argument.ts`: `flowArgument` overloads, default sentinel behavior, marker types, and `isFlowArgument`.
- `src/flow-compose/flow.ts`: `flow(flowContext, flowBody)` wiring. If arguments are declared, returns deferred runner `(input) => ...` and exposes values to runners as nullary `FlowFunction`s.
- `src/flow-compose/flow-function.ts`: `flowFunction(body)` and `flowFunction(partialContext, body)` invoker wiring with local context.

## Type Model

- `Runners`: registry of runnable functions available to a body.
- `FlowFunctionInvoker<R>`: `(runners) => FlowFunction<R>`.
- `FlowContext`: map of invokers or `flowArgument()` markers; undefined entries are skipped.

## Flow Inputs

- Use `flowArgument<T>()` for required input keys.
- Use `flowArgument(defaultValue)` for optional keys with defaults.
- Composed runners accept one input object; inside flows, values are consumed as nullary runner calls.

## Test Coverage Areas

- Single nullary function behavior.
- Local nested `flowFunction` composition without `flowArgument`.
- Required vs default flow arguments.
- Nested function stacks with root `flowArgument`.

# Required Validation Workflow

After each code generation or file edit, run:

- `npm run typecheck`
- `npm run lint`
- `npm run test`

If any command fails, fix the issue and re-run all three until they pass.
